How I Became a Web Developer...

Everything you need to know about my path.

After experiencing the burn out that came with professional video editing, I found myself working under a hosting company. From there I was plucked From tech support to web design and have never looked back since.

Currently I am studying front and backend development so that I can Level up my skillset and have more creative freedom when working on projects.

When I'm Not Coding...

I'm a whirlwind of inner peace.

Off hours you'll find me finding my balance on the yoga mat, foraging in my garden, researching the nutritional value of whatever i'm shoving into my mouth, or giving my cats way too much attention.
